Usage: compile [-c] | [-cpp] FILE

The script compiles .c and .cpp files in a fancy way (Shows all warnings)
If no option is specified, the script finds it automatically.

Options:
 -c		compile C code
 -cpp		compile C++ code
 -h,-?,--help	display this helpp and exit

Exit status:
 0	if OK
 1	if no argument is specified
 2	if the argument is not a file
 3	if the option is not recognised
 4	if there are to many arguments
 5	if the language (c/cpp) is not recognised
